def: A variety; -- used in giving scientific names, and oftenabbreviated to var.
A liquid hydrocarbon found in crude wood spirits.

A kind of oil formerly used in dressing the hair; -- so calledbecause originally obtained from Macassar, a district of the Islandof Celebes. Also, an imitation of the same, of perfumed castor oiland olive oil.
Any aquatic pulmonate gastropod belonging to Planorbis, Limn√¶a,and allied genera; a pond snail.
The doctrine or the practices of the Essenes. De Quincey.

A suffix denoting that which does a thing; an act or process;the result of an act or process; state or condition; as, aliment,that which nourishes, ornament, increment; fragment, piece broken,segment; abridgment, act of abridging, imprisonment, movement,adjournment; amazement, state of being amazed, astonishment.
3d pers. sing. pr. of Find, for findeth. [Obs.] Chaucer.
Something to preserve memory; a reminder; a monument; hence, amark; an image; a superscription; a record. [Obs.] Spenser.
A popular name for any society or club which meets for thepractice of male part songs.
